# SprintCycle Optimization (slim) / 优化规则（精简）

Full reference: `docs/CURSOR_OPTIMIZATION_RULES.md` · Workflow: `docs/SPRINT_OPTIMIZE_WORKFLOW.md` · Guide: `docs/SPRINT_OPTIMIZE_GUIDE.md`  
完整参考与分阶段工作流见上述文档。

## Triggers / 触发词

「删减字段」· 「遵循 DDD 治理」· 「删除兼容逻辑」· 「优化架构」· 「精简代码」· 「前后端对齐」· `/sprint-optimize`

English: consolidate fields · DDD governance · remove compatibility · optimize architecture · refactor · frontend-backend alignment

## Non-negotiable principles / 不可妥协原则

1. **100% logic preservation** — never drop unverified business logic. (业务逻辑完整保留。)
2. **DDD + hexagonal** — align with `sprintcycle-architecture-orchestration.mdc`. (架构合规。)
3. **No compatibility layers** — implement final state in one go; update all call sites (backend + frontend). (禁止过渡兼容层。)
4. **HITL gates** — requirements → PRD approval → technical design approval → then implement (`AskUserQuestion`). (三处 HITL。)
5. **Test before done** — `uv run pytest` + frontend checks; `make ci-local-quick` for medium+ changes. (测试通过再完成。)
6. **Docs sync** — update `README.md`, `README_EN.md`, `docs/ARCHITECTURE_INVARIANTS.md` when behavior/architecture changes. (文档同步。)

## Optimization types / 优化类型

| Type | Action |
|------|--------|
| Field consolidation | Merge semantic fields → unified context; remove legacy fields |
| DDD governance | Fix layer violations; adapters in infra, wiring in composition root |
| Compatibility cleanup | Remove `_legacy_*` / shims; update all importers |
| Frontend-backend alignment | DTO → API → types → store → views in one pass |

## Execution order / 实施顺序

Backend: `domain` → `application` (DTO/services) → `interfaces/http` → tests  
Frontend: `api/` → `types/` → `stores/` → `views/` → lint/build

## Verification checklist (summary) / 验证清单摘要

- [ ] HITL: requirements, PRD, technical plan approved
- [ ] No compatibility code added; legacy removed
- [ ] Backend + frontend synchronized
- [ ] Tests pass; docs updated if needed
- [ ] PR + CI green for submission phase

See `docs/SPRINT_OPTIMIZE_WORKFLOW.md` for full Phase 1–6 checklists. (完整清单见工作流文档。)
